Team A Feature Document Jutoverse –
Government Services Assistance AI
Workspace
1. Program Ingestion &amp; Foundational Document
Alignment
This section outlines the regulatory framework, system preferences, and target parameters
derived from official government data directives.
Document 1: Executive Summary &amp; Program Objective
● Modernization Framework: A joint collaboration between the National Digital
Directorate and JDC Israel under the Government Procurement Administration to
fundamentally optimize the citizen experience in government services.
● Operational Mandate: Establishes an experience environment for government
ministries to test mature advanced AI and automation tools tailored to diverse public
barriers.
● Core Core Service Needs:
○ Document Data Extraction: Transition away from manual reviews by
automatically parsing handwritten or scanned long forms into structured digital
fields. Supports Hebrew and Arabic and avoids redundant document uploads.
○ Form-Filling Assistance: Real-time interactive guidance with physical disability
adaptations to assist low digital literacy populations. Validates and maps data
into Hebrew databases while preserving original audit histories.
○ Frontal &amp; Telephonic Service Translation: Simultaneous two-way voice and
text translation specialized in official government vocabulary across call centers
and public receptions. Prioritizes Arabic, English, Russian, and Amharic.
○ Non-Biometric Citizen Identification (IVR): Replaces legacy identity
verification over phone systems without biometrics by parsing call context,
reading paces, and metadata.
○ Secure After-Hours Digital Access: Round-the-clock context-aware natural
language access to personal files, payment tracks, and request statuses over
digital messaging networks (WhatsApp, web chat, SMS).

● Pilot Parameters: Highly mature solutions execute a rapid trial in an operational test
environment lasting up to two weeks. The budget is strictly capped at 50,000 NIS
(including VAT) per solution to cover minimal architecture adaptation and knowledge
transfer.
Document 2: AI-Powered Research Proposal Review System for
Government Funding

● Operational Initiative: A core challenge scenario issued by the Ministry of Innovation,
Science, and Technology to determine if AI can match human analytical quality in
reviewing complex research proposals.
● Required System Outputs: For every evaluated application, the system must generate
numerical scoring across criteria , a strengths/weaknesses summary , an initial
recommendation passed to the judging committee , and a compiled final report.
● Architectural Dependencies: Native integration preference with the AWS Cloud
ecosystem under the Project Nimbus framework using ready-made managed
environments (e.g., Amazon Bedrock).
● Security &amp; Isolation Mandates:
○ Geographic Sovereignty: All source documents, vector databases, and
embeddings must be hosted and processed exclusively inside the localized
Israeli Region (e.g., AWS il-central-1 or GCP me-west-1).
○ Data Protection &amp; Model Isolation: Implements verified &quot;Opt-Out&quot; settings;
uploaded files or answers are contractually barred from training or improving
external models.
○ Data Destruction: Automatic data wiping of raw source materials immediately
after vector embedding creation and export.
○ Network Isolation &amp; DLP: Runs fully isolated within the ministry&#39;s private Virtual
Private Cloud (VPC) via AWS PrivateLink, requiring Multi-Factor Authentication
(MFA). Automated Data Loss Prevention (DLP) tools (e.g., Amazon Macie) mask
personally identifiable information (PII) prior to model processing.

Document 3: זירת האתגרים הממשלתית – שיפור תהליך העבודה של נציגי השירות
באמצעות כלי בינה מלאכותית (#7190)
● Foundational Call: The initial request launched by the Accountant General ,
Government Procurement Administration , and National Digital Directorate to optimize
the workflows of frontline customer service representatives.
● Procurement Schedule: Establishes the formal timeline parameters for the Request for
Information (RFI) with paid demonstrations:
○ Vendor Briefing Webinar: 29/06/2026 at 10:00.
○ Clarification Questions Deadline: 05/07/2026 at 10:00.
○ RFI Submission Deadline: 12/07/2026 at 18:01.
○ Capability Interview &amp; Demonstration View: 03/09/2026 (Estimated).
Document 4: Description of the Need &amp; Guidelines for Submitting
Responses
● Evaluation Standards: Bilingual requirement matrix mapping technical feasibility for
service representative support tools.
● Core Support Functional Needs:
○ Knowledge Management Streamlining: Deploys conversational semantic
digital assistants to scan dense internal portals, guides, and circulars to produce
verified, source-based answers.

○ Multi-Channel Experience Measurement: Consolidated free-text analysis (topic
classification, sentiment tracking, pain point identification) across emails,
surveys, face-to-face feedback, and call logs to feed live dashboards.
○ Official Translation for Public Reception: Secure, simultaneous voice/text
translation systems tailored specifically for frontal counters serving diverse
language groups (Arabic, Russian, Amharic).
○ Official Translation for Call Centers: Low-latency telephonic integration
mapping speech-to-text and text-to-speech feedback immediately into official
government terminology.

● Compliance Safeguards: Demands full Right-to-Left (RTL) formatting and Hebrew
interface support , web accessibility laws compliance , data privacy protection , and
information security alignment with the Government ICT Authority (Yahav
recommendations).
2. Core Platform Feature Inventory &amp; Interaction Layout
The interactive prototype components are divided across the system&#39;s core operational
interfaces.
2.1 Overview Page Clickable Features
A. Metric System (KPI Dashboard)
● Components: Interactive Metric Cards, KPI Dashboard, System Statistics.
● User UI Action: Click any active Metric Card.
● Expected UI Behavior: The selected card highlights, dynamically filtering database
statistics to let users isolate specific key performance indicators.
● Operational Purpose: Gives program managers an immediate overview of platform
performance (e.g., manual tracking hours saved or IVR recognition success rates).
B. AI Reasoning Panel (Explainability Layer)
● Components: AI Reasoning Panel, Confidence Score Display, Decision Justification
Log.
● User UI Action: Select an interaction record or warning flag tied to an automated AI
choice.
● Expected UI Behavior: The panel displays an AI decision summary, verified model
confidence percentage, an explanation of the underlying factors, and complete audit trail
logs.
● Operational Purpose: Enforces operational transparency, allowing supervisors to audit
and verify automated actions.
C. Signal / Alert System
● Components: Clickable Alert Cards, Live Signal Feed, Warning Notifications.
● User UI Action: Hover over or click an alert card within the activity feed.
● Expected UI Behavior: The targeted alert card is highlighted and reveals contextual
metadata, anomaly specifics, and warning parameters.
● Operational Purpose: Enables early profiling and troubleshooting of operational system
issues or sudden traffic spikes.
D. Feature Banner (System Status Header)
● Components: Global System Status Banner.

● User UI Action: Automatic trigger upon initialization or page refresh.
● Expected UI Behavior: Renders the status of the platform (e.g., “AI Monitoring Active”,
“System Online”, or “No Critical Alerts”).
● Operational Purpose: Provides a clear understanding of system health at a glance.
E. Window Panel Layout System
● Components: Modular Window Panels, Dashboard Layout Grid.
● User UI Action: Navigate the dashboard or adjust browser dimensions.
● Expected UI Behavior: The workspace panels automatically adapt, maintaining layout
organization and responsiveness across different monitor screens.
● Operational Purpose: Enhances information accessibility and satisfies accessibility
design compliance rules.
2.2 Service Operations Page Clickable Features
F. AI Inspector Panel (Sticky Intelligence Layer)
● Components: AI Inspector Panel, Sticky Decision Viewer, Contextual Analysis Panel.
● User UI Action: Select an active request record from the service stream feed.
● Expected UI Behavior: The side panel stays locked in place while scrolling, displaying
automated recommendation texts, confidence parameters, decision rationales, and
supporting context files.
● Operational Purpose: Allows operators to continuously track AI recommendations
without losing visual context while navigating lengthy data tables.
G. Interaction / Action Feed
● Components: Multi-Channel Service Requests, Operational Logs, Interaction History.
● User UI Action: Click an individual interaction row inside the activity feed stream.
● Expected UI Behavior: The clicked row switches to an active state, passing its request
details, status labels, and extraction properties directly into the AI Inspector Panel.
● Operational Purpose: Serves as the central operational workspace to monitor public
service entries.
H. Operational Drill-Down Panels
● Components: Full-Width Expanded Analytics Panels, Deep-Dive Investigation Views,
Detailed Case Records.
● User UI Action: Click an interaction flagged for manual review or advanced verification.
● Expected UI Behavior: Sub-panels expand downward, revealing granular processing
records, historical system interactions, data analytics charts, and internal review logs.
● Operational Purpose: Facilitates exhaustive case tracking and troubleshooting of
complex anomalies from a single dashboard view.
I. AI Reasoning Integration
● Components: AI Reasoning Integration Box, Confidence Logic Tracker, Central
Explainability Component.
● User UI Action: Toggle between different interactions in the activity feed.
● Expected UI Behavior: The integrated box updates in real time, synchronizing model
justifications and confidence percentages with the active selection.
● Operational Purpose: Ensures a reliable and uniform explainability standard across all
operational dashboard workspaces.
2.3 Jutoverse – Representative Assistant AI Workspace Features


[ JUTOVERSE AI WORKSPACE GRIDS ]
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
───
1. Live Transcription Panel ──&gt; Speech-to-Text browser API stream.
2. Real-Time Translation Panel ──&gt; Live language mapping via LibreTranslate.
3. AI Reasoning Panel ──&gt; Contextual summary outputs.
4. Intent Detection Panel ──&gt; Auto-categorizes entries (e.g., Inquiry).
5. Conversational Workspace ──&gt; Representative-to-Assistant chat interface.
6. Grounded Answer System ──&gt; Citation and confidence metrics processing.
7. Evidence &amp; Citation Panel ──&gt; Reference indices for auditing.
8. Translation Assist ──&gt; Source-to-target transaction history tracking.
9. Live Support Signals Panel ──&gt; Core sentiment and text risk analytics.
● Live Transcription Panel: Converts citizen audio frequencies into text live via browser
SpeechRecognition hooks. Emits text data across the workspace once a phrase
terminates.
● Real-Time Translation Panel: Asynchronously processes source data to target outputs
via LibreTranslate integrations, generating an AI Suggested Actions map.
● Grounded Answer &amp; Citation Engine: Maps responses directly to verifiable reference
indices and circular files to ensure absolute trustworthiness.
● Live Support Signals Panel: Evaluates interaction risks and tracks citizen sentiment
patterns live using a color-coded severity grading scale.
